            <title>[LOG4J2-3070] ensure EncodingPatternConverter#handlesThrowable is implemented</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-3070</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Guess the title is enough to understand what happens &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
 Long story short the handlesThrowable() logic to skip forced (by default) append of the exception does not work as soon as encoding is used which is almost always the case when outputing JSON/XML using PatternFormatter (since Json appender required 3rd party libs which are often undesired).&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/473&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;This PR&lt;/a&gt; implements this method by checking the nested formatters.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
